@NODE "MAIN" "ListPrefs.Guide"

         @{fg shine} ___________________________________________________________@{fg text}
         @{fg shine}|@{fg text}                                                           |
         @{fg shine}|@{fg text}                      @{fg shine}@{b}  Preferences  @{ub}@{fg text}                      |
         @{fg shine}|@{fg text}                  for @{b}FileTypeList@{ub}.dopus5                  |
         @{fg shine}|@{fg text}                  and @{b}FileTypeIcons@{ub}.dopus5                 |
         @{fg shine}|@{fg text}___________________________________________________________|



              @{" FileTypeIcons.prefs " rx "/ARexx/Check SYS:Prefs/FileTypeIcons.prefs 1.0"} und @{" FileTypeList.prefs " rx "/ARexx/Check SYS:Prefs/FileTypeIcons.prefs 1.0"}

              are preferences-programs
              for FileTypeIcons.dopus5 and FileTypeList.dopus5
              They should be found in SYS:Prefs/
              Click on the buttons above to test this.

              If this test was sucessful,
              you can start the prefsprograms
              by using the mainprograms` menues.

              By using the following buttons
              you can start the prefsprograms from here:

              @{" FileTypeIcons.prefs " rx " /Prefs/FileTypeIcons.prefs"}     @{" FileTypeList.prefs " rx " /Prefs/FileTypeList.prefs"}



         ___________________________________________________________________@{fg shine}
         -------------------------------------------------------------------@{fg text}

         If you have just installed or updated one of the main-programs
         on their startup the here described preferencesprograms will appear
         and write prefs-files to ENV: and ENVARC:
         Simply quit them using 'Cancel'.

         ___________________________________________________________________@{fg shine}
         -------------------------------------------------------------------@{fg text}


         @{"" ""}@{bg shine}  GUI elements  @{bg back}@{"" ""}



         @{FG shine}@{b}Window height@{ub}@{FG text}

           Minimum amount of list entries to display.
           This determines the height of the main window.
           (min.3, max.31, default 8)

         @{b}@{FG shine}Window width@{FG text}@{ub}

           This in one of the factors affecting the windows
           width.
           If this valua is too high, the main window could
           perhaps not even appear.
           (min.20, max.86, default 56)

         @{fg shine}@{b}List-Name@{ub}@{fg text} (String-Gadget)

           The shown list will be saved
           using this path and this filename.

         @{fg shine}@{b}Non-Filetypes@{ub}@{fg text} (String-Gadget)

           In FileTypeIcons the (not shown) list of non-filetypes
           will be saved as textfile using this path and filename.
           Using that button in FileTypeIcons,
           this list will be shown immediately.

           In FileTypeList the non-filetypes
           are placed at the bottom of the filetypes-list,
           and will be saved with that list.

         @{fg shine}@{b}Filetypes-Directory@{ub}@{fg text} (String-Gadget)

           Usually this is DOpus5:filetypes/
           If you didn`t select a different filetypes-directory,
           the filetypes in this directory will be read.

           Do only change this path for experimntal purposes,
           and only, if you exacly know, what you do !
           Afterwards do not use the 'Save'-button, but click at 'Use'.

         @{fg shine}@{b}______________________________________________________________@{ub}@{fg text}
         ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

         @{" Snapshot " rx "/ARexx/SystemReq The button:*n*n- Snapshot -"}

           This permanently saves the current dimension
           and position of the program-window.

           If you didn't start the prefs program
           from within the list-program`s menue,
           you`ll be told to run the list-program.

           ATTENTION:
           If you do not do this, and if you click on 'continue',
           the prefs-window seems to be frozen,
           but it is just waiting for you to start the list-program.
           Simply do it ;-)


           If you start the prefs program from within
           the list-program, please position the program`s
           window *before* choosing this function in
           order to permanently snapshot it.

           To unsnapshot the window, simply delete the
           file
           @{" ENVARC:Triton/ " rx "/ARexx/Lister ENVARC:Triton FileTypeIcons.win.1 FileTypeList.win.1 SOURCE"} FileTypeList.win.1
           or FileTypeIcons.win.1
           This directory is created in ENV: as well as
           in ENVARC: the very first time any triton
           program is quit.
           The particular file in question is created
           in ENV: when you quit the program for the
           very first time and will be copied to ENVARC:
           when you use the snapshot function.

           You can, by the way, snapshot any application
           using Triton.library (including all FileTypeUtils)
           by using the @{" Triton " SYSTEM "SYS:Prefs/Triton"} prefs program.
           To do this, start the application and than
           start Triton-Prefs, where you should mark
           the program to be snapshot and then take a
           look at the "Windows" division.


         @{" Fonts " SYSTEM "SYS:Prefs/Font"}

           This gadget will run the Workbench`s
           font preferences program.

           '@{fg shine}@{b}Default Text setting ...@{ub}@{fg text}'
           determines the font used for the @{b}gadgets@{ub}
           and the @{b}string gadgets@{ub},
           thus taking influence on the @{b}width of the main window@{ub}

           '@{fg shine}@{b}System Text setting ...@{ub}@{fg text}
           determines the text used for the @{b}file list@{ub}.


         @{" Triton " SYSTEM "SYS:Prefs/Triton"}

           The Triton prefs program offers some further
           preferences options.




         _____________________________________________________________@{fg shine}
         -------------------------------------------------------------@{fg text}

         @{"" ""}@{bg shine}  Menu functions  @{bg back}@{"" ""}


         @{b}Help@{ub}

           switches the help text on/off.

           Note 1:
           Choosing this menu option will save
           all current preferences after checking
           their validity, including of course
           the status of this menu option.

         @{b}Guide@{ub}

           displays this guide

         @{fg shine}@{b}____________________________________________@{ub}@{fg text}
         ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

         @{b}Load previous@{ub}

           Loads the settings which have been set
           with "Use" or "Save" earlier.

         @{b}Load default@{ub}

           Loads the default settings

         @{b}Load again@{ub}

           Reloads the settings
           In case you hit the wrong keys :-)

         @{fg shine}@{b}____________________________________________@{ub}@{fg text}
         ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

         @{b}Save Use Cancel@{ub}

           Does exactly the same as the gadgets
           at the bottom of the prefs-window.

           Please note that before
           the program quits, the settings
           will be validated.
           Thus the delay ;-)
           If an error occurs,
           a requester will appear,
           the window will stay open
           and no settings will be saved.
           The settings also won't be saved
           if no settings have been changed.

         _____________________________________________________________@{fg shine}
         -------------------------------------------------------------@{fg text}






@ENDNODE

